CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1969, pg. 7 reads: "Off To Rome - This picture was taken of Miss Jessie Holmes as she boarded a plane at the Greater Pittsburgh Airport for Rome. Miss Holmes was among the Pittsburghers attending the ceremonies at the Vatican which elevated Bishop John Wright to a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church."
TitMainTitle: Jessie Holmes wearing double breasted suit with leopard patterned cuffs and collar, standing at bottom of stairs of TWA airplane at Greater Pittsburgh Airport
